<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,937,1576]" pageId="11" pageNumber="378">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,368,1045,1071]" pageId="11" pageNumber="378">Identification.</emphasis>
Species with only one pair of tubercles in post median part of elytra, these tubercles also prominent, similar in shape and size to tubercles in sub-basal part (
<figureCitation box="[900,1031,1081,1107]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[209,1383,185,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-19@12.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 30–34. Merarius holzschuhi Frieser, holotype male, SW Bhutan, Gedu; 30, dorsal habitus; 31, pronotum in dorsal view; 32, head in dorsal view; 33, right antenna, dorsal view; 34, lateral habitus [left hindtibia and hindtarsus omitted from the picture]. Scale bars in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223442/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="378">Figs 30, 34</figureCitation>
). All tubercles in sub-basal and post median part conical with blunt tops rather upwardly oriented. Disc of pronotum completely flat without any imprint (
<figureCitation box="[160,242,1153,1179]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[209,1383,185,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-19@12.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 30–34. Merarius holzschuhi Frieser, holotype male, SW Bhutan, Gedu; 30, dorsal habitus; 31, pronotum in dorsal view; 32, head in dorsal view; 33, right antenna, dorsal view; 34, lateral habitus [left hindtibia and hindtarsus omitted from the picture]. Scale bars in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223442/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="378">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
). Dorsal transverse carina of pronotum in contact with lateral carina rounded, not forming protruding lateral lobes (
<figureCitation box="[229,316,1189,1215]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[209,1383,185,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-19@12.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 30–34. Merarius holzschuhi Frieser, holotype male, SW Bhutan, Gedu; 30, dorsal habitus; 31, pronotum in dorsal view; 32, head in dorsal view; 33, right antenna, dorsal view; 34, lateral habitus [left hindtibia and hindtarsus omitted from the picture]. Scale bars in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223442/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="378">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
). Elytra and pronotum with predominance of dark brown to blackish colour. Small tufts of light coloured dense appressed setae mainly on elytra, lateral part of pronotum and pronotal declivity, the same pattern also on lower side of body. Elytral declivity with narrow tortuous transverse light-coloured stripe. Body size 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.05" pageId="11" pageNumber="378" unit="mm" value="8.05">8.05 mm</quantity>
(only 
<typeStatus box="[268,366,1297,1323]" pageId="11" pageNumber="378">holotype</typeStatus>
male known). Colour pattern as in 
<figureCitation box="[762,933,1297,1323]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[209,1383,185,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-19@12.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 30–34. Merarius holzschuhi Frieser, holotype male, SW Bhutan, Gedu; 30, dorsal habitus; 31, pronotum in dorsal view; 32, head in dorsal view; 33, right antenna, dorsal view; 34, lateral habitus [left hindtibia and hindtarsus omitted from the picture]. Scale bars in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223442/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="378">Figs 30–31, 34</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
